  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects include:\n\n1. Required reporting of suspicious financial transactions\n\n2. Customer due diligence procedures\n\n3. Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n\n5. International cooperation to detect and prevent money laundering\n\nOrganizations like financial institutions must comply with these regulations, which vary by jurisdiction but generally aim to detect and prevent financial crimes.",
